dct_description_sm: Relief shown by 10 metres contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by isolines. Distric boundaries, walls, telegraph lines, three classes of roads, railroads, paths, areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some streets and buildings are named.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : War Office by the Geographical Section, General Staff, 1927.
